let unsorted = new Array();

Object.keys( allRepeatCuts ).map( function( key ) { unsorted.push( allRepeatCuts[key] ) });

let sorted = unsorted.sort( function(a, b) {
	if ( a.name &gt; b.name ) {
		return 1;
	} else if ( a.name &lt; b.name ) {
		return -1;
	} else {
		return 0;
	}
});

				<string>RepeatCut.callback
********************
Define a callback shortcut that is called immediately after running the primary shortcut. The results of the primary shortcut are sent to the callback function. If the callback returns the string ❌❌❌, we exit out of the repeat loop. Otherwise we use the output of the callback function as input to the primary shortcut and continue the loop (after waiting the duration of the run interval). </string>
